“The media which is so directly complicit in a smear campaign against my mother took notice of your actions of resistance, so too did this narrative begin to change. The world saw that a young generation unafraid of the power of the establishment was ready to challenge its lies.” She says the new generation is now reminded of how she touched so many on a personal level. The two of daughters of the late Winnie Madikizela-Mandela have struggled to hold their emotions as they pay tribute to their mother at Orlando Stadium Saturday morning. Zenani Mandela-Dlamini says her mother’s life was a remarkable one – she meant a lot to the whole world. Mandela-Dlamini says there is no other way she would have loved her mother to be remembered more than the way South Africans have shown since her passing.
